the assassin was then required to hit the target one more time within a space of from 4.8 to 5.6 seconds.
the Commission concluded that Oswald was capable of accomplishing this second hit even if there was an intervening shot which missed.
thereby leaving a time span of 4.8 to 5.6 seconds between the two shots which struck their mark.
